oscillation spectra, and transiting planet parameters. The method
exploits structure in the problem when the covariance function is
expressed as a mixture of complex exponentials, without requiring evenly
spaced observations or uniform noise. This form of covariance arises
naturally when the process is a mixture of stochastically driven damped
harmonic oscillators—providing a physical motivation for and
interpretation of this choice—but we also demonstrate that it can
be a useful effective model in some other cases. We present a
mathematical description of the method and compare it to existing
scalable GP methods. The method is fast and interpretable, with a range
of potential applications within astronomical data analysis and beyond.
We provide well-tested and documented open-source implementations of
this method in C++, Python, and Julia.},
